# Kill all Python servers on port 8222
netstat -ano | findstr :8222
taskkill /PID <PID> /F

# Restart Uvicorn
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8222

1️⃣ Kill the stuck process

From your netstat output, the PID is 22048 (the Uvicorn server). Kill it:

taskkill /PID 22048 /F


Check again:

netstat -ano | findstr :8222

It should be gone.

2️⃣ Optional: Kill all python processes

Sometimes multiple zombie Python servers are running:

taskkill /IM python.exe /F


(Be careful if you have other Python scripts running.)

3️⃣ Restart Uvicorn on a clean port

After killing the old processes:

uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8222
